  "takeaway": [
    "Part A documents 5 models x 2 axes of default quartile+no-analog strata; stratum labels rise from most-similar (S0) to the NaN no-analog top bin, and base correctness falls monotonically with novelty on every model.",
    "Part B: zero-frontier cell counts are {'nbins2_quantile': 7, 'nbins4_quantile': 11, 'nbins6_quantile': 12, 'fixed_edge_02_04_06_08': 10} across binnings (fractions {'nbins2_quantile': 0.467, 'nbins4_quantile': 0.44, 'nbins6_quantile': 0.4, 'fixed_edge_02_04_06_08': 0.333}, all near 0.4); the novel-tail infeasibility frontier survives every quantile and fixed-edge binning choice, so it is not a bin artifact.",
    "Part C: within-ligand-stratum pocket-median splits show a consistent residual gap (median 0.243, 20/20 cells with the familiar-pocket half more correct) -- ligand bins do not absorb pocket novelty, which is why two-axis stratification is warranted."
  ]
